
[1]lamentable

   LAM'ENTABLE, a. [L. lamentabilis.]

   1. To be lamented; deserving sorrow; as a lamentable declension of
   morals.

   2. Mournful; adapted to awaken grief; as a lamentable tune.

   3. Expressing sorrow; as lamentable cries.

   4. Miserable; pitiful; low; poor; in a sense rather ludicrous. [Little
   used.]
